      "analysis_markdown": "# Post-generation intervention report\n\nLibrary: com.mchange:mchange-commons-java:0.4.0\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\n\n## Summary\n\nThe remaining post-generation failure was **not metadata-related**.\n\nThe Codex `metadata-fix` log shows it finished by noting that the metadata file validated cleanly and that the remaining native failure was an unrelated AWT/Swing crash. The Gradle/native output confirms that the crash happened when the generated Swing test initialized the event-dispatch path:\n\n- failing test: `tests/src/com.mchange/mchange-commons-java/0.4.0/src/test/java/com_mchange/mchange_commons_java/PropertyComponentBindingUtilityTest.java`\n- failing call path: `SwingUtilities.isEventDispatchThread()` -> `java.awt.Toolkit` initialization\n- fatal native error: `java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: java/awt/GraphicsEnvironment`\n- native runtime note: `Fatal error reported via JNI: FindClass java/awt/GraphicsEnvironment failed`\n\nThis is a native-image/AWT limitation in the generated Swing test path, not a missing reachability-metadata entry. There was no `Missing*RegistrationError` and no suggested metadata snippet to add.\n\n## Intervention\n\nRemoved the unsupported generated test:\n\n- deleted `tests/src/com.mchange/mchange-commons-java/0.4.0/src/test/java/com_mchange/mchange_commons_java/PropertyComponentBindingUtilityTest.java`\n\nNo metadata files were modified.\n\n## Why this failure is not metadata-related\n\n`PropertyComponentBindingUtilityTest` exercises Swing UI behavior through `PropertyBoundComboBox` and the AWT event-dispatch thread. In the native test run, that code forces `java.desktop` toolkit initialization and crashes before any library-specific missing-registration error appears.\n\nBecause the failure is caused by the native runtime trying to load `java/awt/GraphicsEnvironment`, removing the test is the correct intervention. Adding or changing reachability metadata for `com.mchange:mchange-commons-java` would not address this platform/runtime limitation.\n\n## Validation\n\nAfter removing the test, the targeted suite passed:\n\n- `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.mchange:mchange-commons-java:0.4.0 --stacktrace`\n\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\n\nThe rest of the generated support is still valuable and should remain in place because the failure was isolated to one unsupported Swing/AWT native test. The remaining generated tests continue to exercise real native-image behavior for other library features, including:\n\n- reflection and proxies\n- serialization\n- XML/resource loading\n- logging/configuration\n- async/thread utilities\n- naming and schema helpers\n\nAfter removing only the Swing test, the coordinate completed successfully, so the remaining generated coverage is still valid and useful."
