      "intervention_file": "post-gen-interventions/org.apache.kafka_kafka-streams_3.6.0.md",
      "analysis_markdown": "# Post-generation intervention report\n\nLibrary: org.apache.kafka:kafka-streams:3.6.0\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\n\n## Summary\n\nThe post-generation native test failure was caused by two generated dynamic-access tests that exercise upstream Kafka test classes relying on Mockito's default ByteBuddy mock maker. In Native Image, ByteBuddy tries to define `net.bytebuddy.utility.Invoker$Dispatcher` at runtime, which is an unsupported runtime class-definition feature rather than a missing metadata registration.\n\nBased on the Codex metadata-fix log, the earlier metadata gaps had already moved forward enough that they were no longer the blocking failure. The remaining blocker was the unsupported Mockito/ByteBuddy runtime behavior, so the generated tests that depended on that behavior were removed. No metadata files were modified.\n\n## Root cause of each failing test\n\n### 1. `org.apache.kafka.streams.processor.internals.ReadOnlyTaskTest.shouldThrowUnsupportedOperationExceptionForForbiddenMethods()`\n\n- **Root cause:** not metadata-related.\n- **Why:** the failure is `com.oracle.svm.core.jdk.UnsupportedFeatureError` caused by Mockito/ByteBuddy attempting runtime class generation for `net.bytebuddy.utility.Invoker$Dispatcher`.\n- **Action taken:** removed generated test `tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-streams/3.6.0/src/test/java/org_apache_kafka/kafka_streams/ReadOnlyTaskTestDynamicAccessTest.java` and its test-only reflection config `tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-streams/3.6.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/read-only-task-test-dynamic-access/reflect-config.json`.\n\n### 2. `org_apache_kafka.kafka_streams.ReadOnlyTaskTestDynamicAccessTest.shouldExerciseReadOnlyTaskReflectionCoverage()`\n\n- **Root cause:** follow-on failure, not metadata-related.\n- **Why:** this generated wrapper test launches the failing upstream `ReadOnlyTaskTest` method and then asserts that the launched test had zero failures. Since the upstream test fails due to ByteBuddy runtime class definition, the wrapper reports `expected: 0L but was: 1L`.\n- **Action taken:** removed with the same file deletion above.\n\n### 3. `org.apache.kafka.streams.state.internals.RocksDBStoreTest.shouldCloseStatisticsWhenUserProvidesNoStatistics()`\n\n- **Root cause:** not metadata-related.\n- **Why:** the primary failure is again Mockito/ByteBuddy runtime class definition in Native Image, not a missing registration. The suppressed `NullPointerException`s in teardown are cleanup fallout after setup never completed.\n- **Action taken:** removed generated test `tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-streams/3.6.0/src/test/java/org_apache_kafka/kafka_streams/RocksDBStoreTestDynamicAccessTest.java` and its test-only reflection config `tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-streams/3.6.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/rocksdb-store-test-dynamic-access/reflect-config.json`.\n\n### 4. `org_apache_kafka.kafka_streams.RocksDBStoreTestDynamicAccessTest.shouldExerciseRocksDBStoreStatisticsLookup()`\n\n- **Root cause:** follow-on failure, not metadata-related.\n- **Why:** this generated wrapper test launches the failing upstream `RocksDBStoreTest` method and then asserts zero failures. Because the launched test fails for the same Mockito/ByteBuddy native-image limitation, the wrapper fails with `expected: 0L but was: 1L`.\n- **Action taken:** removed with the same file deletion above.\n\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\n\nThe remaining generated support still provides useful native coverage for `kafka-streams` without depending on unsupported Mockito/ByteBuddy runtime class generation. After removing only the two problematic generated tests and their test-only configs, `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.kafka:kafka-streams:3.6.0 --stacktrace` passed successfully.\n\nThat preserved support still validates meaningful reflection and resource usage through the remaining generated tests, including:\n\n- `IQv2IntegrationTestDynamicAccessTest`\n- `IntegrationTestUtilsDynamicAccessTest`\n- `KStreamImplDynamicAccessTest`\n- `QueryableStateIntegrationTestDynamicAccessTest`\n- `TaskAssignorIntegrationTestDynamicAccessTest`\n- `KafkaStreamsTest`\n\nSo the correct intervention here was to remove only the non-portable generated tests, while keeping the rest of the generated support intact."
    },
